race.comment: The $3 million 3YO Guineas. NINJA (1) couldn't have been more impressive taking out the G3 Vo Rogue by a whopping five lengths last time out and winning rider Berry stays in the stirrups. The step-up to the 1400m should suit and only needs some luck navigating from the carpark draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. ICARIAN DREAM (11) made up some ground to hit the frame in the Gold Edition at the latest outing and will have come on with that run in the locker. Poses a serious threat. MEMO (10) has placed two from two when second-up and gets McDonald on board from a middle draw. Capable of a big performance. SPANISH TREASURE (6) shed the maiden tag over this track and trip last time out and will have derived some confidence from that breakthrough victory. In the mix. O' OLE (2) won the 2YO edition of this race last year and can feature if he brings his A-game.
